// =============================================================================
// NIRI MAIN CONFIGURATION FILE
// =============================================================================
// Main entry point for Niri window manager configuration
// Written in KDL (KDL Document Language) - a human-friendly config format
//
// MODULAR STRUCTURE:
// This file imports modular configuration files for better organization
// Each aspect of Niri is configured in its own dedicated file
//
// CONFIGURATION MODULES:
// - input.kdl: Mouse, touchpad, keyboard input settings
// - keybindings.kdl: Keyboard shortcuts and hotkeys
// - outputs.kdl: Monitor configuration and layout
// - layout.kdl: Window tiling behavior and rules
//
// EDITING:
// After changes: home-manager switch --flake .#niri
// Or just: systemctl --user restart niri (if only KDL files changed)
//
// DOCUMENTATION:
// See: https://github.com/YaLTeR/niri/wiki/Configuration:-Overview
// =============================================================================

// Import input device configuration (mouse, keyboard, touchpad)
include "input.kdl"

// Import keybinding configuration (all keyboard shortcuts)
include "keybindings.kdl"

// Import monitor/output configuration (display settings)
include "outputs.kdl"

// Import window layout configuration (tiling behavior)
include "layout.kdl"


